This week on Backpacker TV:  Steve and Jordan head to Montana where they get a behind the scenes look at the Mystery Ranch backpack building process before hitting the Continental Divide Trail with Oboz’ Rich Hohne, and Steven Reinhold and Earl Hunter from Black Folks Camp Too where they discuss the importance of inclusivity in the outdoors and the power of the Unity Flame.

Introducing the Sawyer Tap Filter, a new addition to Sawyer’s line of high-performance water filtration systems. 

The Sawyer Tap Filter removes biological contaminants, guaranteeing immediate clean drinking water when you need it most. Great to use when traveling, during boil alerts, or in emergencies when safe drinking water is compromised, the Tap Filter is easy-to-use and will filter to up to 500 gallons of clean drinking water per day.

It’s the ideal component for use during natural disasters such as floods, hurricanes, fires, and earthquakes. Hitting the road? Consider the Tap Filter your pocket-sized peace of mind for all questionable sources –– campgrounds, festivals, events, in RVs, and when traveling internationally.

Backpacker Skills Editor, Zoe Gates and Editor-in-Chief, Shannon Davis share their picks for alternatives to fire when camping and backpacking.  Did you know 87% of forest fires are started by humans?  Sad, but true.  When you're in an area that doesn't allow fires, or when the conditions are too dangerous for a campfire, consider one of their picks as a fun way to bring your hiking and camping friends together to "spark" the conversation without the need for a real campfire.

Sand dune surfing in Colorado!  Canyoneering and packrafting (with the dogs!) in Utah!  This week's episode of Backpacker Get Out More TV is an adventure you don't want to miss!  Watch Now: https://bit.ly/3dUlDOZ #bptv #getoutmore #utah #colorado #sandsurfing #canyoneering #packrafting
